==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[cetus|cētus]]'', a "[[sea monster]]" from {{Gr.}} [[Κητώ]] (L. [[Ceto]]), mother of the [[Gorgon]]s.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Cetus}}
'''Cetus'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[whale]].  It includes the star [[Mira]].

